   122→## New features …
   126→### Arrays and unary tuples …
   128→#### `P.array(pattern)`
   130→To match an array of elements, you can now use `P.array`:
   131→
   132→```ts
   133→import { match, P } from 'ts-pattern';
   134→
   135→const responsePattern = {
   136→  data: P.array({
   137→    id: P.string,
   138→    post: P.array({
   139→      title: P.string,
   140→      content: P.string,
   141→    }),
   142→  }),
   143→};
   144→
   145→fetchSomething().then((value: unknown) =>
   146→  match(value)
      →…
   157→### Optional object properties …
   159→#### `P.optional(pattern)`
   161→If you want one of the keys of your pattern to be optional, you can now use `P.optional(subpattern)`.
   162→
   163→If you `P.select()` something in an optional pattern, it's type will be infered as `T | undefined`.
   164→
   165→```ts
   166→import { match, P } from 'ts-pattern';
   167→
   168→const doSomethingWithUser = (user: User | Org) =>
   169→  match(user)
   170→    .with(
   171→      {
   172→        type: 'user',
   173→        detail: {
   174→          bio: P.optional(P.string),
   175→          socialLinks: P.optional({
   176→            twitter: P.select(),
   177→          }),
      →…
